-- Risanamento sells Paris properties to Chelsfield for 1.2 bln eur
-- 
-- Fri Jan 24, 2014 02:56AM EST
-- None



MILAN, Jan 24 (Reuters) - Italian property company Risanamento <RN.MI> said on Friday it had accepted an offer from Chelsfield/The Olayan Group to buy a portfolio of property located in Paris for 1.225 billion euros ($1.68 billion).

In a statement Risanamento said it would cash in more than 230 million euros after stripping out debt relating to the property when the deal closed.